PRACTICAL 4: Using Standard Switches
Prerequisites

• Practical 1 and 2 completed
• ESXi host connected to vCenter

Steps

Log in to vSphere Client using browser.

Navigate to Networking and view existing standard switches.

Create a new Standard Switch with default MTU size.

Create a Virtual Machine Port Group on the switch.

Assign physical network adapter if required.

Save the configuration.

Edit VM settings and attach the VM to the new port group.

Verify network connectivity of the virtual machine.
